    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-08-04T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-08-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="335"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d335">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.00F/134</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum From the Italian Embassy</hi>
                    <note n="2" xml:id="d335fn2">Left with the Under Secretary of State by the
                        Italian Ambassador on August 4, 1932.</note>
                </head>
                <p>In relation to the letter addressed to Secretary <persName corresp="#p_SHL1"
                        >Stimson</persName> on August 1st 1932 by the Leaders of Anti-Fascist
                    Italo-American groups it is to be observed: <list>
                        <label>1)</label>
                        <item>the charge against the Royal Italian authorities to carry out a
                            Fascist propaganda in the United States is so notoriously unfounded that
                            it need not be disproved;</item>
                        <label>2)</label>
                        <item>the “Federazione del Littorio” has absolutely no official character
                            nor has it any connection either with the Representatives of the Fascist
                            Party in Rome nor with the Royal diplomatic and Consular Officials in
                            this country;</item>
                        <label>3)</label>
                        <item>the statement that Vice Consuls <persName corresp="#p_CGU1"
                                >Carodossi</persName> and <persName>Castellani</persName> have in
                            any way taken part in or been present at the riot in the train from
                            Staten Island on July 4, is false. In fact Signor <persName
                                corresp="#p_CGU1">Carodossi</persName>
                            <hi rend="italic">was not on the train</hi>, having taken the trip to
                            Staten Island and back, by motor in company with Consul General
                                <persName corresp="#p_GE2">Grazzi</persName>. As to Signor
                            Castellani, who was travelling on the train, he did not witness the
                            shooting as he was in the third, and not in the second car in which the
                            incidents culminating in the killing of <persName corresp="#p_AS1"
                                >Salvatore Arena</persName> took place.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p>Concerning the arrest of Mr. <persName corresp="#p_TD1">Domenico
                        Trombetta</persName> on charge of murder, no comment can be made, the case
                    being in the hands of the <pb facs="0546" n="456" xml:id="pg_456"/> Judicial
                    authority, whose sentence is pending; however, circumstances seem to strongly
                    indicate that the whole matter is a sinister scheme of <persName
                        corresp="#p_TD1">Trombetta</persName>’s enemies.</p>
                <closer>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-08-04">August 4,
                            1932</date>.</dateline>
                </closer>
            </div>
